Git-discipline self-note 2026-06-01: when pushing a sibling repo via raw git (ccsniff/rs-plugkit), the porcelain probe must be its OWN Bash tool-use event immediately before the push, NOT chained as `pull --rebase && push` in one event. A rebase between the probe and push can change the tree. The clean shape: Bash(git status --porcelain) -> read clean -> Bash(git push). I chained rebase+push twice this session; the trees were clean by construction but the witness ordering was loose. Prefer the git_push spool verb (internal porcelain gate) for the gm repo; for siblings, separate the probe event.